#{\footnote display}${\footnote Display options}K{\footnote Display options;Rotate display}
{\f4\fs30\b Display options}
\plain \f4\fs20
\par
\par
It is possible to rotate the display through 360 degrees (in ninety degree steps) using the Options|Display menu. It is also possible to 'flip' the display, so enabling full rotation of the display to any desired position.\par
\par
Click the radio buttons to obtain the desired rotation (measured anti-clockwise) from the default zero degrees assumed from the datafile. Toggle the check box to flip/unflip the display. Once you are happy with the desired rotation you may wish to print the \plain \ul\f4\fs20 Nonogram\plain \ul\v\f4\fs20 typnono\plain \f4\fs20  out, using the File|\uldb\f4\fs20 Print\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 print\plain \f4\fs20  menu option.\par
\par
\par\b\f4\fs24
Also See
\par\plain \uldb\f4\fs20
Printing Nonograms\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 print\plain \uldb\f4\fs20\par
Contents\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 main_contents\plain
\page 

#{\footnote print}${\footnote Printing Nonograms}K{\footnote Print;Printing Nonograms}
{\f4\fs30\b Printing Nonograms}
\plain \f4\fs20
\par
\par
\plain \ul\f4\fs20 Nonograms\plain \ul\v\f4\fs20 typnono\plain \f4\fs20  may be printed out to any selected printer using the File|Print menu option. The program will automatically size the print-out to fit the default paper size, and submit the print job to the Windows Print Manager. If there are any problems in creating the print-out, the program will display an appropriate error message.\par
\par
\par\b\f4\fs24
Also See
\par\plain \uldb\f4\fs20
Display options\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 display\plain \uldb\f4\fs20\par
Contents\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 main_contents\plain
\page 

#{\footnote changes}${\footnote Changes for Windows}K{\footnote Changes for Windows;Nonogram Solver v1.0 for DOS;Upgrading from DOS}
{\f4\fs30\b Changes for Windows}
\plain \f4\fs20
\par
\par
If you have used the Nonogram Solver v1.0 for DOS, you will be able to quickly adapt to this new Windows version. The same fast solve routines are still available, and are more easily accessible. Screen display of \plain \ul\f4\fs20 Nonograms\plain \ul\v\f4\fs20 typnono\plain \f4\fs20  has been improved, and a print option added. \par
\par
However, the use of four letter commands to drive the program has been dropped. They are replaced by alternative versions under Windows. The following list details the old commands and their new equivalents.\par
\par
\b\f1\fs18
ALTR \plain \f4\fs20 - Options|\uldb\f4\fs20 Display\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 display\plain \b\f1\fs18 \par
CATA \plain \f4\fs20 - File|Open \b\f1\fs18 \par
CHDR \plain \f4\fs20 - File|Open \b\f1\fs18 \par
COMM \plain \f4\fs20 - no longer required \b\f1\fs18 \par
FILE \plain \f4\fs20 - File|Open \b\f1\fs18 \par
HELP \plain \f4\fs20 - Help \b\f1\fs18 \par
PARS \plain \f4\fs20 - Options|\uldb\f4\fs20 Pars\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 pars\plain \b\f1\fs18 \par
SOLV \plain \f4\fs20 - Options|Solve \b\f1\fs18 \par
TITL \plain \f4\fs20 - no longer required \b\f1\fs18 \par
VARS \plain \f4\fs20 - Options|\uldb\f8\fs20 Solution\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 solution\plain \f4\fs20 \par
\par
\par\b\f4\fs24
Also See
\par\plain \uldb\f4\fs20 
Display options\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 display\plain \uldb\f4\fs20 \par
Solution options\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 solution\plain \uldb\f4\fs20 \par
Data parsing\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 pars\plain \uldb\f4\fs20 \par
Contents\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 main_contents\plain
\page 

#{\footnote pars}${\footnote Data parsing}K{\footnote Data parsing}
{\f4\fs30\b Data parsing}
\plain \f4\fs20
\par
\par
The data parse menu option allows you to check a datafile for inconsistencies before solving takes place. A data parse takes place automatically every time before a solve, so it is normally unnecessary to use this option.\par
\par
The data parse method simply checks that the number of 'blocked' squares along each side of the Nonogram is the same. If they are not, a message is displayed and no attempt is made to solve the Nonogram.\par
\par
Typical errors highlighted are :-\par
\par
\tab Running two numbers together (eg 76 instead of 7 6) \par
\par
\par\b\f4\fs24
Also See
\par\plain \uldb\f4\fs20
Solution options\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 solution\plain \uldb\f4\fs20\par
Contents\plain \uldb\v\f4\fs20 main_contents\plain
\page 

